snippet.textDisplay: Hi I’m a math major in college, saw ur vid on finals just wanted to say that you can calculate the determinate on a calculator (Ti-84 or higher) it’s get tricky when it become a 3x3 matrix on paper but via calculator it’s seamless. regardless, orthogonality and null space is such a difficult concept to grasp orthogonality deals with vectors being perpendicular when their dot product is 0 & null space when any matrix A consists of all the vectors B such that AB = 0 and B is not zero.
